      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is completely valid to feel that this is something much deeper than a temporary patch; the loss of your vibrant self sounds immense. Naming this feeling as a \"funeral\" suggests a true sense of profound grief for who you once were. Please honor the weight of that loss, and know that it is okay to not feel or see anything right now. If you are struggling to hold onto anything, reaching out to a professional therapist can offer a safe space to navigate this intense mourning.",
      "source": "target",
